AWARD-WINNING actress and TV presenter Nomzamo Mbatha has been announced as one of the hosts for the Global Citizen reunion concert. The talented media personality, who recently appeared in international movie Coming 2 America, will co-host alongside musician Selena Gomez. She took to social media to share the good news. “The news is out; we are hosting the biggest reunion concert. I will be joining the global citizen Vax Live concert to amplify the message on vaccine equity,” she said. According to the organisation, the much-anticipated concert is aimed at ensuring equitable access to Covid-19 vaccines around the world by calling on world leaders to donate surplus Covid-19 vaccines, or make financial commitments to vulnerable countries. ALSO READ | BABES 'MISLED' MPINTHSO Furthermore, it is said that the event will bring together world leaders, artists, and more, featuring performances by Jennifer Lopez, Eddie Vedder, Foo Fighters, J Balvin, H.E.R, and more to support global vaccine equality, inspire confidence in Covid-19 vaccines. It will also encourage people to get their shots when they can. The concert will take place on 8 May at SoFi Stadium in Los Angeles, California and will air globally. The concert is part of the organisation’s year-long Recovery Plan for the World campaign, which was launched in February as a road map to prosperity and recovery during and following the pandemic, prioritising health, hunger, education, environment, and equity. A post shared by Nomzamo Mbatha ???? (@nomzamo_m) 